[thinking] **Evaluating class resource accessibility**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering how TypePool.Default.of(targetClassLoader) uses getResourceAsStream with a custom loader to read class files. It seems like, in a native image, class resources, like `.class` files, may not be available unless explicitly included. I wonder if existing native tests have left out the necessary test class resources. This is important to think about when dealing with native images and their resource management.
[thinking] 
