[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class resource accessibility**\n\nI’m considering how TypePool.Default.of(targetClassLoader) uses getResourceAsStream with a custom loader to read class files. It seems like, in a native image, class resources, like `.class` files, may not be available unless explicitly included. I wonder if existing native tests have left out the necessary test class resources. This is important to think about when dealing with native images and their resource management.\n\n**Considering Byte Buddy usage**\n\nI'm exploring how to handle class files using Byte Buddy in a native image context. It seems that `.class` resources might not be included for app classes by default, which could lead to failures in reading test classes at runtime. I wonder if the existing tests are relying on Byte Buddy generation rather than TypePool. I need to find an alternative way to construct an unloaded TypeDescription programmatically without these resources. Should I look into using TypeDescription.Latent? Let's check the constructors!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00b419bd9b341aa70169f1a6e24b4081979b322d39f8abc46a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8abss0kpRTvPbvM-Zrtvk3bLCGko0UBWQRFE_-c70aCMiu1CfVhETlOAEMZ7Pj0hrLjv-3N0hIpjok_qJo_cbqhUcHw1kSaeSOdwVyRZ619Dh5zK33nNn1jScGlsmtjYIiMqRwlC6UHIKo_ppwlR2ZLTzsi_kfHph_nnB_6944zKVya1AGiYRBrfa_UlfeHuQlWd6K4EdbaesjqrP9mDx5G2AjFWH129oRTFEkQHZgh_BgvxkWFvai8YqAHWdxI4cDqMy-SA-fp0osKpS4ClAQDvJr_DALv2Oi6E8UTB1is0TsaBBXPjxeFKX0DR3ECheJOJyLFzr26OHRNGS1HWtStJY3ixgrFhN0DxpVXETxiokWeBElllZZWaynBdIU_HM1xMvGQ0S68oaZJsgLY7NZDOgQsgTqDStM1Qm99OWYLUmnoLrnly2EUemzVotXqEMKvbhnC4pc1sf5s-tGrYWAZTJDYgbSjNrST4NgIVk67QzENkueSZ2nA-72uwFvk82XROgbqIbqHL75eO90qmNncOu2YGZEBvZ7p3GiLM2XYgp0JQ7JsUSw_FdtLG2RliqcqEWBFW6KYu9Mxw20zyUIuJoMNs9jEtQIfFLe0TEY5-MKnWqpdLMZ_UAMA17jaW-kg2sxhnZDh70bpXKcWKBj4bU5p_zIK2bbR-XUno9M-8qtMKQng7lBKCDr9ZL7eOqJTLRmpN9nm_R